An Act to protect open space, historical resources, and community housing from coastal threats.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 2 of chapter 44B, as appearing in 2020 Official Edition, is hereby amended by
2 striking out the definition "preservation" in line 66 and inserting in place thereof the following
3 definition:-
4 ''Preservation'', protection of personal or real property from injury, harm or destruction,
5 including but not limited to the construction, alteration, or rehabilitation of beaches, dunes,
6 seawalls, and other coastal infrastructure for the purpose of protecting open space, historical
7 resources, or community housing from flooding, sea-level rise, and storm surge.
